# Security Rules

## Never expose
Never log or return password fields, even hashed.
Never include stack traces in API responses.
Never hardcode credentials, tokens, or secrets — use process.env.
Never commit .env files.

## Auth
JWT tokens must be validated in middleware before route handlers access req.user.
Protect /tasks and /projects routes with the auth middleware.
Public routes: POST /auth/register, POST /auth/login, GET /health.

## Input
Always validate and sanitize input before passing to services.
Never interpolate user input directly into SQL strings.
Use parameterized queries ($1, $2) for all DB queries.
